s reference points to calculate positions accurate to a matter of meters. In fact, with advanced forms of GPS logistics team can make measurements to better than a centimeter! These days GPS is finding its way into cars, boats, planes, construction equipment, movie making gear, farm machinery, even laptop computers. To understand exactly why it is so useful and important, we should first look at how GPS works and to understand working of GPS System first we have to understand the different segment of GPS system. GPS Technical Architecture.  1.There are at least 24 operational GPS satellites at all times  2.GPS receivers placed in vehicle will catches the signal from different satellites. It requires signal from at least 3 satellites to calculate its current positions; GPS receiver do not transmit  3.The signals, moving at the speed of light, arrive at a GPS receiver at slightly different times because some satellites are farther away than others. The distance to the GPS satellites can be determined by estimating the amount of time it takes for their signals to reach the receiver  4.After calculating the position, time and speed receiver transmits the data to the desired control room through GSM or GPRS  5.Various applications at control room do the operation of that data and finally plot the location on MAPS  6.After plotting the location on map any number of clients can see the location of vehicles using internet","Url":"http://www.trackwithus.com/","Started On":"Feb 2010","Finished On":"Feb 2013"},{"Title":"Radioobuddy","Description":"RadiooBuddy is android application that play online radio.This application play music from anywhere in the world where internet is present based on gprs connection. ","Url":"http://www.radioobuddy.com/","Started On":"Aug 2012","Finished On":"Dec 2012"},{"Title":"HRM (Human Resource Management)","Description":"Human resource management, desktop solution for company HR, to manage employee ( three different companies) track their leave 